headline.main: Syrian Fighting Gives Hezbollah New but Diffuse Purpose

docs.abstract: Diplomatic Memo; Kai Bird book The Good Spy: The Life and Death of Robert Ames, which spotlights 1983 suicide bombing of American Embassy in Beirut, Lebanon, reveals that Ali Reza Asgari, Iranian intelligence officer who oversaw bombing, defected in 2007 to United States, where he still lives under CIA protection; Asgari was given asylum because he held critical information about Iran's nuclear program; disclosure is timely, given US is in critical phase of nuclear negotiations with Iran.
